id: pm-9y8q
title: "Deduplicate comments, notes, and learnings command stacks"
description: "Duplicate audit 2026-05-22: jscpd found src/cli/commands/comments.ts, notes.ts, and learnings.ts repeat the same item lookup, add/list option handling, output shape, and mutation/history patterns. Representative clones include comments.ts:2-14 vs notes.ts:1-13, comments.ts:58-77 vs notes.ts:46-65, comments.ts:193-206 vs notes.ts:115-128, learnings.ts:1-15 vs notes.ts:1-15, learnings.ts:43-65 vs notes.ts:43-65, and learnings.ts:119-132 vs notes.ts:115-128. Search found closed implementation/parity work (pm-c465, pm-v1s1) but no active dedupe task. Fix by extracting a shared append/list annotation command factory for comments, notes, and learnings with resource-specific metadata/history labels."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: annotations,code-quality,commands,dedup
created_at: "2026-05-22T18:59:53.812Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-24T01:58:49.896Z"
author: codex-duplication-audit
acceptance_criteria: "comments/notes/learnings share one command core for item resolution, append/list modes, author/message handling, and output rendering; resource-specific behavior remains explicit through adapters; existing comments, notes, and learnings tests pass; pnpm build passes."
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: "Closed by extracting the shared annotation command core for comments, notes, and learnings."
expected_result: "Annotation commands share list/add, limit, author, mutation, rendering, and ownership plumbing while keeping command-specific input and audit semantics."
actual_result: "src/cli/commands/annotation-command.ts now owns the shared core; comments, notes, and learnings delegate to it; focused tests, manual dogfood, validate, and full release gate passed."
